# CorpusCriste — Deploy

## Routes

1. Next.js App Router routes = folder structure under `app/`
2. Navbar options = `specs/routes.json` (use `parent` for dropdown children)
3. **Never** configure Vercel-only routes without matching `app/` and `specs/routes.json`

## New nested route

Create `app/{section}/{slug}/page.tsx` and register in specs.

## Legacy redirects (vercel.json)

```json
{
  "redirects": [
    { "source": "/slug-antigo", "destination": "/secao/novo-slug", "permanent": true }
  ]
}
```

When renaming public URLs, add a permanent redirect.

## Deploy flow

Push to GitHub → Vercel detects Next.js → `npm run build`

Static assets (`public/`, `_next/static/`) are cached automatically by Vercel/Next.js. Do not add custom `headers` regex patterns in `vercel.json` — path-to-regexp rejects patterns like `/(.*\\.(png|jpg))`.
